(8301, 'paclitaxel', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Caution should be exercised when paclitaxel is concomitantly administered with known substrates (e.g, midazolam, buspirone, felodipine, lovastatin, eletriptan, sildenafil, simvastatin, and triazolam), inhibitors (e.g., atazanavir, clarithromycin, indinavir, itraconazole, ketoconazole, nefazodone, nelfinavir, ritonavir, saquinavir, and telithromycin), and inducers (e.g., rifampin and carbamazepine) of CYP3A4.', 'DailyMed'),
