(1390, 'carbidopa levodopa', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Iron salts and dopamine D2 antagonists including metoclopramide: May reduce the effectiveness of DHIVY ( 7.2, 7.3) 7.1 Monoamine Oxidase (MAO) Inhibitors The use of nonselective MAO inhibitors with DHIVY is contraindicated [see Contraindications (4) ]. 7.3 Iron Salts Iron salts or multivitamins containing iron salts can form chelates with levodopa and carbidopa and can cause a reduction in the bioavailability of DHIVY. If iron salts or multivitamins containing iron salts are co-administered with DHIVY, monitor patients for worsening Parkinson’s symptoms.', 'DailyMed'),
