(1664, 'elvitegravir, cobicistat, emtricitabine, and tenofovir disoproxil fumarate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Sedative/hypnotics: Benzodiazepines:e.g.Parenterally administered midazolamclorazepatediazepamestazolamflurazepambuspironezolpidem ↑ sedatives/hypnotics Concomitant use of parenteral midazolam with STRIBILD may increase plasma concentrations of midazolam.', 'DailyMed'),
(1664, 'mirtazapine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Patients should be made aware of a potential increased risk for serotonin syndrome if concomitant use of mirtazapine tablets with other serotonergic drugs, including triptans, tricyclic antidepressants, fentanyl, lithium, tramadol, buspirone, tryptophan and St.', 'DailyMed'),
