(25705, 'sodium chloride, soldium lactate, potassium chloride and calcium chloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'The risk of hyperkalemia is increased in patients treated with agents or products that can cause hyperkalemia or increase the risk of hyperkalemia, such as potassium-sparing diuretics (amiloride, spironolactone, triameterene), with ACE inhibitors, angiotensin II receptor antagonists, or the immunosuppressants tacrolimus and cyclosporine.', 'DailyMed'),
